Package: statdown
Title: Use R in Your Static Site Without Replacing Your Static Site Generator
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Andrew", "Stryker", , "axs@sdf.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Renders R Markdown files to CommonMark that any static site
    generator can consume directly — no Pandoc, no second HTML engine.
    Handles htmlwidget dependencies (deduplication, CDN delivery, SRI
    integrity) via 'depkit' so interactive widgets work without giving up
    control of your site's build pipeline.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://andrewjstryker.github.io/statdown/,
    https://github.com/andrewjstryker/statdown
BugReports: https://github.com/andrewjstryker/statdown/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
